    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-16T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="756"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d756">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">892.61317/4–1646: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Siam</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Yost</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">immediate</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-16T12:00:00+07:00"
                            >April 16, 1946—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:31 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>400. ReDeptel’s 145, March 7 and 195 March 27.<note n="45" xml:id="d756fn1"
                        >Neither printed.</note> Tripartite agreement, Memorandum Understanding and
                    accompanying notes presented yesterday to Foreign Minister by Thompson<note
                        n="46" xml:id="d756fn2">Geoffrey H. Thompson, British Minister in
                        Siam.</note> and self. Foreign Minister confident there would be no
                    disagreement on substance of drafts and promised to give final reply very
                        promptly.<note n="47" xml:id="d756fn3">Telegram 425, April 23, 3 p.m., from
                        Bangkok advised that the Siamese had proposed a number of minor amendments
                        but only two of any substance. In telegram 312, the following day, the
                        Department stated that it had no objections to these amendments.
                        (892.61317/4–2346)</note> Thompson has not yet received from London final
                    texts exchange of notes re revision Article 14, formal agreement, but expects
                    them hourly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Yost</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
